<p>Brazil’s federal police arrested former president Jair Bolsonaro on Saturday after a Supreme Court justice deemed him a flight risk, with authorities suspecting he planned to flee to avoid starting a 27-year prison sentence for leading a coup attempt [bbc.com#1][pbs.org#2][abcnews.go.com#2][ndtv.com#1][apnews.com#1]. Video released by the Supreme Court shows Bolsonaro acknowledging he used a soldering iron on his electronic ankle monitor “out of curiosity” [scmp.com#1][theguardian.com#1][firstpost.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. Justice Alexandre de Moraes ordered Bolsonaro into preemptive custody, ruling he violated house arrest by breaking his ankle monitor [apnews.com#1][abcnews.go.com#2]. The arrest came days before his 27-year sentence was to begin [cbsnews.com#1][pbs.org#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/JKGm2cz45BveD_ik-YAPaJTr5_GEPaYolGf0C_rmuyHR3n0p19JMObjZx1Qz81RsvYwriqsax9KCsCu8rnoYmnWmvkHFiwFM-NinE__fFhMhxgUWtJ0IsoFs9MfBoVgT_bm9Q7FaxX_gwvGViVkXZlNA_K8R3Vy_QWB3LWo6zA' alt='Brazil’s ex-president Jair Bolsonaro' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Tag tampering: Court-released footage shows Bolsonaro saying he applied a “hot iron” and, when asked if it was an iron, replying “No, a soldering iron,” and saying it was “out of curiosity.” The plastic casing appeared scorched, while an officer said the core mechanism seemed intact [scmp.com#1].</li><li>Court order: Supreme Court justice Alexandre de Moraes ruled Bolsonaro violated house arrest by breaking his ankle monitor and ordered preemptive custody [apnews.com#1][abcnews.go.com#2].</li><li>Flight-risk factors: A judge noted the proximity of Bolsonaro’s residence to the U.S. embassy in Brasília when assessing flight risk [straitstimes.com#1].</li><li>Sentence context: Bolsonaro faces a 27-year prison term after conviction for leading a coup attempt linked to the Jan. 8, 2023 events in Brasília [abcnews.go.com#2][cbsnews.com#1][ndtv.com#1][japantoday.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>No, a soldering iron. - Jair Bolsonaro</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Jair Bolsonaro: In court-released video, he acknowledged using a soldering iron on his ankle monitor “out of curiosity.” (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/22/far-right-former-president-jair-bolsonaro-arrested-in-brazil'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Justice Alexandre de Moraes: He ordered Bolsonaro into preemptive custody, ruling he violated house arrest by breaking his ankle monitor; Bolsonaro was also deemed a flight risk. (<a href='https://apnews.com/article/brazil-bolsonaro-prison-arrest-d68ae43b99762c577efe7e6ba20b0542'>AP News; BBC News</a>)</li><li>Brazil’s federal police: They arrested Bolsonaro on suspicion he planned to flee to avoid beginning a 27-year prison sentence. (<a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/bolsonaro-arrested-over-alleged-plot-to-escape-and-avoid-27-year-prison-term-in-brazil'>PBS NewsHour</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/ex-brazilian-president-bolsonaro-arrested-over-flight-risk-9683580#publisher=newsstand'>Ex-Brazilian President Bolsonaro Arrested Over Flight Risk</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3333835/brazils-bolsonaro-damages-ankle-monitor-soldering-iron-out-curiosity'>Brazil’s Bolsonaro damages ankle tag with soldering iron ‘out of curiosity’</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/22/far-right-former-president-jair-bolsonaro-arrested-in-brazil'>Jair Bolsonaro arrested after tampering with ankle tag ‘out of curiosity’</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/news-wrap-bolsonaro-arrested-days-before-starting-prison-sentence-over-coup-attempt'>News Wrap: Bolsonaro arrested days before starting prison sentence over coup attempt</a> - pbs.org</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ce8qdm5zg10o'>Jair Bolsonaro arrested after being deemed a flight risk</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://a